title: Photograph, "Tammany Hall at 14th Street", 1875
medium: Collodion prints mounted on yellow cardboard
inscribed: Verso: printed label: This building, on 14th street was occupied by Tammany Hall from1868 to 1927.
description: View of the building seen from across the street. Depicts a three story building, the roof surmounted by an elaborate niche containing a statue.

tombstone.epitaph: Photograph, "Tammany Hall at 14th Street", 1875. Collodion prints mounted on yellow cardboard. 1947-107-1.
